OL,3,CWilliam congratulates England on 'top
OL,4,Cperformance' as fans celebrate 2-1
OL,5,Cvictory
OL,7,FWriting on X, Sir Keir tagged
OL,8,FNorwegian prime minister Jonas Gahr
OL,9,FStore, writing: "Norway 1 ` 2 Jude
OL,10,FBellingham. @JonasGahrStore, your boys
OL,11,Ftook one hell of beating."
OL,13,FEngland fans in Miami were in a
OL,14,Fjubilant mood, with many hoping to
OL,15,Fextend their trip to go to Atlanta for
OL,16,FEngland's semi-final.
OL,18,FScott Bickerton, 33, from Solihull,
OL,19,Ftold the Press Association: "We're
OL,20,Fgoing to win it, aren't we?
OL,26,@qD@QOUsD@ZO]{D@]OU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1783849731
OL,3,CWilliam congratulates England on 'top
OL,4,Cperformance' as fans celebrate 2-1
OL,5,Cvictory
OL,7,F"This is the year, we're going to win
OL,8,Fit. I'm confident."
OL,10,FAsked what makes him confident, Mr
OL,11,FBickerton said: "Bellingham.
OL,12,FBirmingham City, world class."
OL,14,FHis friend Ashley Wager, 32, from
OL,15,FBirmingham, said: "Bellingham again.
OL,16,FSaves the day again."
OL,18,FHe added: "It's coming home, we're
OL,19,Fgoing to do it."
