OL,3,CWilliam congratulates England on 'top
OL,4,Cperformance' as fans celebrate 2-1
OL,5,Cvictory
OL,7,FJamie Smith, 31, from Birmingham,
OL,8,Fsaid: "Shaky first half but dug deep.
OL,10,F"Jude saved us again."
OL,12,FAlex Jay, 45, from Birmingham, said
OL,13,Fthe match was "a tough watch" but
OL,14,F"they turned it around and did what
OL,15,Fthey had to do".
OL,17,FRussell Osborne, 34, from Birmingham,
OL,18,Fsaid: "I think we've got it this year.
OL,19,FThe team spirit's there, the
OL,20,Fconfidence is there."
