OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1783849731
OL,3,CWilliam congratulates England on 'top
OL,4,Cperformance' as fans celebrate 2-1
OL,5,Cvictory
OL,7,FKish Kerai, 34, said the match was
OL,8,F"electrifying" but that he planned to
OL,9,Fgo home and sleep.
OL,11,FHe said: "I had doubts but I feel like
OL,12,FEngland have courage and they have
OL,13,Fheart, which you can't replace and
OL,14,Fnothing on paper will ever be able to
OL,15,Freplace that."
OL,17,FSome 1,600 football fans wearing St
OL,18,FGeorge's flag bucket hats packed out
OL,19,Fthe north-west London venue, where
OL,20,Fthey sang football chants and songs as
OL,21,Fthey prepared for the match.
OL,26,@pD@AOUpD@NO]sD@JOUwD@NO]
